FT  22 MAY 92 / World News in Brief: Shark stays put
Bill Heine won a six-year planning battle to keep an 18 ft glass fibre shark
on the roof of his Oxford home when the Department of the Environment upheld
his appeal against an Oxford City Council order. The DoE inspector said the
system must make some small allowance for 'the dynamic, the unexpected and
the downright quirky.'
